@startuml Communication_Protocol_Sequence
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title <size:16><b>Communication Protocol Sequence</b></size>\n<size:12><i>Multi-Layer Protocol Stack Overview</i></size>

participant "STM32" as STM32
participant "UART Link\n115200 baud\n8N1" as UART
participant "ESP32" as ESP32
participant "MQTT Protocol\nv5.0\nQoS 0/1" as MQTT
participant "MQTT\nBroker" as Broker

== Command Flow (Web → STM32) ==
note over Broker, STM32 #E3F2FD: <b>Downstream Command Path</b>

Broker -> MQTT: PUBLISH datalogger/stm32/command
activate MQTT
MQTT -> ESP32: MQTT message
activate ESP32
deactivate MQTT

ESP32 -> ESP32: Route by topic
ESP32 -> UART: Text command + '\n'
note right of ESP32: Plain text format:\n"SINGLE\n"\n"PERIODIC ON\n"\n"PERIODIC OFF\n"
activate UART
deactivate ESP32

UART -> STM32: UART RX interrupt
activate STM32
deactivate UART

STM32 -> STM32: Parse and execute
deactivate STM32

== Data Flow (STM32 → Web) ==
note over STM32, Broker #FFF9C4: <b>Upstream Data Path</b>

STM32 -> STM32: Collect sensor data
activate STM32
STM32 -> UART: JSON + '\n'
note right of STM32: JSON format:\n{"mode":"SINGLE",\n"timestamp":1729699200,\n"temperature":30.59,\n"humidity":73.97}
activate UART
deactivate STM32

UART -> ESP32: UART RX interrupt
activate ESP32
deactivate UART

ESP32 -> ESP32: JSON parse
ESP32 -> MQTT: PUBLISH with QoS
note right of ESP32: Topic routing:\n- datalogger/stm32/single/data\n- datalogger/stm32/periodic/data
activate MQTT
deactivate ESP32

MQTT -> Broker: Forward message
deactivate MQTT

== State Synchronization ==
note over ESP32, Broker #E8F5E9: <b>State Persistence</b>

ESP32 -> ESP32: State change detected
activate ESP32
ESP32 -> MQTT: PUBLISH with retain=1
note right of ESP32: Retained message:\n{"device":"ON",\n"periodic":"OFF",\n"timestamp":...}
activate MQTT
deactivate ESP32

MQTT -> Broker: Store retained
activate Broker
deactivate MQTT

Broker -> Broker: Persist state
note right of Broker: New clients receive\nlast known state
deactivate Broker

== MQTT Status Notification ==
note over ESP32, STM32 #FFEBEE: <b>Connection Status Sync</b>

ESP32 -> ESP32: MQTT state change
activate ESP32
ESP32 -> UART: "MQTT CONNECTED" or\n"MQTT DISCONNECTED"
note right of ESP32: Simple status commands\nfor STM32 mode switching
activate UART
deactivate ESP32

UART -> STM32: Command
activate STM32
deactivate UART

STM32 -> STM32: Switch TX mode
note right of STM32: CONNECTED: live transmission\nDISCONNECTED: SD buffering
deactivate STM32

@enduml